# CollegeDiscover — College Discovery Platform

A full-stack college discovery and comparison platform built with Next.js, TypeScript, Prisma, and PostgreSQL.

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Frontend | Next.js 14 (App Router), React, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS |
| Backend | Next.js API Routes, TypeScript |
| Validation | Zod |
| ORM | Prisma |
| Database | PostgreSQL (Neon) |
| Auth | JWT + bcrypt |
| Deployment | Vercel + Neon |

## Features

- **College listing + search** — full-text search across name, city, state with filters for type, rating, fee range. Paginated results.
- **College detail page** — complete info with courses, placement history, and student reviews via tabs.
- **Compare colleges** — side-by-side comparison of 2–3 colleges across all key metrics.
- **Auth + saved colleges** — JWT-based registration/login, save and manage a personalized college list.

## Getting Started

### 1. Clone and install

```bash
git clone <your-repo>
cd college-platform
npm install
```

### 2. Set up environment variables

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

Fill in your values in `.env`:

```
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://..."   # from Neon
JWT_SECRET="your-secret-key"
```

### 3. Set up the database

Create a free PostgreSQL database at [neon.tech](https://neon.tech), copy the connection string.

```bash
npm run db:push    # push schema to DB
npm run db:seed    # seed with sample college data
```

### 4. Run locally

```bash
npm run dev
```

Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000)

