### Auth

#### `POST /api/auth/register`

```json
{ "name": "John Doe", "email": "john@example.com", "password": "securepassword" }
```

**Response:**
```json
{ "user": { "id": "...", "name": "John Doe", "email": "john@example.com" }, "token": "jwt..." }
```

---

#### `POST /api/auth/login`

```json
{ "email": "john@example.com", "password": "securepassword" }
```

**Response:** Same as register.

---

### Saved Colleges

All saved-college routes require `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header.

#### `GET /api/saved`
Returns list of saved colleges for the authenticated user.

#### `POST /api/saved`
```json
{ "collegeId": "..." }
```

#### `DELETE /api/saved?collegeId=...`
Removes a college from saved list.

